vari-1995.xml	20	Lateral ethmoid [The lateral ethmoid of most characiforms bears a blade-like ventral process that forms the anterior wall of the orbit. Various groups in the order have the medial portion of the ventral blade expanded into a flattened process, typically capped with cartilage, that contacts a comparable cartilaginous process of the palatine. When present, such articular surfaces on the lateral ethmoid in characiform outgroups are round or only slightly transversely elongate and small relative to the main body of the ventral wing.
